---

In my opinion, the most important thing I learned was emotional intelligence. I did not take classes for it, I learned and practiced all day everyday while socializing and participating in group projects. Emotional intelligence is what allows you to work well in groups, to get along with people, and to succeed in a leadership position. There have been several recent studies saying that emotional intelligence is more important then IQ when hiring a new employee. They go on to build better relationships, have more resources and ultimately more influence. Which is a good thing since we need more emotionally intelligent, high status individuals, especially in government. 
Emotionally intellegent people make better leaders and co-workers. They are better able to understand other people, what motivates them and how to interact with them to get things done. They are better suited to work through differences and sort out problems.
